nodes.title: 3) Input Any Refined Image with Face Visible
Crashing Error
widgets_values:
If your workflow is crashing here, then MediaPipe is not able to detect a face here. 

This error can also happen when there is a body turn around, or overlapping. 
 
Manually skip this portion... It can't be swapped.

Copy the refined images in place of these skipped ones.

nodes.title: Facial Detection
widgets_values:
1) Eyes, Mouth, Pupil, Eyebrows Buttons: 

Enable them if you want to swap them too. Mouth is enable by default. 


2) Face: Do Not Enable this, it makes a line around the face borders. And also gives incomplete fill, which will look flickering after swap.  



*Crop Factor - Crops the Face Area, Leave it at 20.

*Bbbox fill - It will make a box around the Face, Do not enable this, it will look ugly after swapping. 

*Dilation - Expands the mask borders. (10 - 20 is fine)

nodes.title: Mask Grow and Blur
widgets_values:
1) You can additionally Expand with this, although the dilations from above has already did the expansion.

2) Blurring the mask give soft blending between the edges. (20 is default, blurring is controlled by "kernel size") Â

nodes.title: Optional Mask Saving
widgets_values: Unmute this Group, and it will also export a mask folder, if you want to color correct in post.

nodes.title: Swapped_A
widgets_values:
*This has more accurate mouth capture, but no color matching.

*You can use masks to color match in after effects and then export those color corrected frames and then Finally render in face fix file for more harmony.    



 

*You can manually color match the Original Frames with the Refined rendered frames to Get both Sync and Color Accuracy which will be then rendered in the #4_1_Face Fix workflow.

nodes.title: Swapped_B
widgets_values:
*This has less accurate mouth capture, but good color matching.

Use this, if you do not need accuracy. Then Finally render them in face fix for getting harmony/Blending. 

The swapped edges will be blended more better in the face fix workflow.

nodes.title: 3) Process
widgets_values: Here, for example only masks of mouth are procced and placed back to the original cropped out area.

nodes.title: 2) Process
widgets_values:
Here, Face is detected for MediaPipe Processor, 

it can't handle far away faces, so cropping is done first.

nodes.title: 1) Process

The Original Frames are being swapped by a refined frame, by this stylized face is swapped with the original
*Preserving the LipSync

nodes.title: 5) Process
widgets_values:
Now Every Stylized Face with Preserved Lip Sync from #1 is Masked out and Put on Refined images. 

This is before color matching.

nodes.title: 6) Process
widgets_values:
Now Every Images from #5 is color matched by the reactor node while preserving the lip sync to some extent. 

Try decreasing the Codeformer weight if it helps or not. but it will introduce flickering.

nodes.title: #4 LipSync Swapper v1.0
widgets_values:
How to Use: 

1) Input Original and Refined Images in the 1 and 2 Directory Nodes.

2) Input 1 Single image from the Refined images, which has closed mouth for better results.  

3) Enter Output folder location. 

5) Enter Batch Range (10 - 20 is fine)

6) Lap Counter skip frames automatically when set to "increment" for final rendering. Use Manual when needed. 

7) [Optional] Change settings if you want, default is good for close up and medium shots.

nodes.title: CONS
widgets_values:
1) This workflow will only work for Realistic or Semi realistic Renders only; it will fail on cartoon or 2d anime faces.

2) Far Shots may sometimes fail or produce bad results.

3) If face is not there/blurred or hidden by hands or a body turnaround is happening, it will give error, manually skip those frames after error.  

4) If the Original Images have very different colorskin, Harsh lighting change then it will be also visible in Final Output, Color Match approximately the original frames to the refined then use.


For Example, you have realistic hulk face in refined but original frames are human skin, then Output will have Hulk face with human lips. To fix this you have 2 options: 
 A - Color Match the original to green or near green then use this workflow. 
 B - By Unmuting the Masks saving option and using these masks to color correct after the final output 

Then the final Output is harmonized by rendering through the #4_0 Face Fix workflow
